                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.55
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The targets were made from enriched",
                "methyl iodine (CH3I). The target thickness was",
                "measured to be about 37 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detector consists of a 4-in. diameter",
                "by 6-in. long NaI(Tl) crystal surrounded by a shield",
                "of NE 102 plastic scintillator used in anticoincidence."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "G"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma-ray detection system used in",
                "present experiment was designed to overcome some of",
                "the difficulties encountered in radiative capture",
                "studies. The entire detector is surrounded by a minimum",
                "of 4 inches of lead to provide additional cosmic ray",
                "shielding. To achieve the cleanest possible spectra",
                "while keeping the dead time to a minimum, the",
                "anticoincidence and pileup suppression requirements",
                "are handled with nanosecond-range electronics."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PGS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The differential cross sections for the 15.11",
                "and 12.71 MeV gamma rays were calculated from a",
                "comparison of the yield from the (3He,gamma) reaction",
                "with the yield from the (p,gamma) reaction on the",
                "same target."
              ]
            }
          ],
